                            <h4><i class="icon-users"></i>Meeting Techniques</h4>
                            <p>Relevant language, vocabulary and phrases are taught, but more importantly, the ability to use them congruently.</p>
                            <p><strong>Required qualifications:</strong> General English level of Intermediate or higher.</p>
                            <p><strong>Number of participants:</strong> Up to 12.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="two-third last">
                            <ul class="unordered">
                                <li>Wake up the brain. A series of exercises and narratives to maximize participants’ receptiveness and learning capacity.</li>
                                <li>Listening skills. Exercises in listening carefully.</li>
                                <li>Sensory acuity. Learn how to listen for clues as to how your colleagues represent their world. How to pick up on non-verbal cues.</li>
                                <li>Rapport. Establishing rapport immediately is vital when it comes to convincing people or influencing their behavior.</li>
                                <li>Pacing and leading. How to use rapport to influence behavior.</li>
                                <li>Anchors. Basic training about anchors. How to recognize them, how to create them and how to maintain them.</li>
                                <li>Use the PEGASUS model to run a meeting efficiently.</li>
                                <li>Use the MYOUR and PEGASUS acronyms for effective negotiations.</li>
                                <li>Learn about the META model for cleaner, more effective communication.</li>
                                <li>Convincer strategies.</li>
                                <li>Who are the characters in a typical meeting? Meet Ivan the Aggressor, Fran the Facilitator and friends.</li>
                                <li>Pattern interrupt. How to subtly put an end to unconstructive behavior.</li>
                                <li>Meeting simulation.</li>
                                <li>Brilliance squared. Learn how to control your own state of mind and always be ready when meeting time comes.</li>
                                <li>Cultural issues.</li>
                                <li>Some golden rules.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
