                            <h4><i class="icon-pencil"></i>Professional Writing Skills with NLP</h4>
                            <p>Relevant language, vocabulary and phrases are taught, but more importantly, the ability to use them congruently.</p>
                            <p><strong>Required qualifications:</strong> General English level of Intermediate or higher.</p>
                            <p><strong>Number of participants:</strong> Up to 12.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="two-third last">
                            <p><strong>Course structure:</strong> 2 days, each consisting of four 1½ hour sessions. Each session will include the use of metaphor to illustrate the topic, intensive information, followed by exercises. Each day will end with an induction to enhance the course’s learnings and ensure that participants take away the maximum benefit and the skill set to use what they’ve learnt.</p>
                            <ul class="unordered">
                                <li>Wake up the brain. A series of exercises and narratives to maximize participants’ receptiveness and learning capacity. Dissolving old beliefs which disrupt your communication.</li>
                                <li>Well-formed outcomes. Learn to specifically formulate your goals, evaluating them from every possible angle. Understand fully what the reader is requesting.</li>
                                <li>Structuring. Learn how to structure your writing so that it is logical and flows well from one section to the next. Using anchors to reinforce your writing.</li>
                                <li>Precise language. Learn how to be extremely clear and precise in your language. Take responsibility for your communication.</li>
                                <li>General to specific. How is your information presented? In very general terms or very specific terms? Take full control of this aspect of your writing and use it to communicate in the most effective way.</li>
                                <li>Good spelling techniques. You can use a spellchecker, but the ability to control your own spelling also gives you the ability to evaluate the structure of what you’ve written, in terms of sentences and paragraphs.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
